		h3 To bring social enterprises into the mainstream!
	.jumbotron
		h2 Who are we? 
		p 
			strong ChooseSocial.PH 
			| is your destination to discover and explore the social enterprise scene in Philippines (and the amazing people behind it!). We are a crowdsourced social directory and aim to be the most comprehensive and up-to-date resource for anyone looking to learn more about social enterprises in Philippines. 
		p 
			|Want to learn about a particular organization, looking for an organization to support, or maybe just feel like shopping while supporting a worthwhile cause? 
			strong ChooseSocial.PH 
			| has got you covered. 
	h2 About the Team
	.whitebox
		.row
			.col-lg-3.col-md-3.col-sm-4.col-xs-12
				.text-center.team
					img(src="/images/gelainesantiago.jpg",class="img-responsive",alt="Gelaine Santiago")
			.col-lg-9.col-md-9.col-sm-8.col-xs-12
				h3 Gelaine Santiago
				p Gelaine is one of the founders of ChooseSocial.PH and is all about people – she believes that effective people management can transform social enterprises into impactful and sustainable sources of good. She has an undergraduate degree in Biology and Political Science, and a post-graduate degree in Human Resource Management in Toronto. She is a Certified Human Resource Professional (CHRP) in Canada and has more than 4 years of experience working within for-profit and non-profit organizations. Gelaine has particular expertise in talent acquisition (recruitment), volunteer management, and training and development, as well as exposure to talent branding, marketing, and employee relations. 
				br 
				p When she's not working as a Talent Acquisition Specialist for a financial firm, she volunteers to give pro bono employment and job search advice to recent immigrants and is also a Member of the Board of Directors for a non-profit humanitarian organization in Toronto focused on mass atrocity prevention. Though she was raised in Canada, she is a proud Filipina (originally from Malolos), and actively searches for ways to help develop strong communities back home. 

				br
				address
					span.fa.fa-twitter
					strong  Twitter
					br
					a(href="https://twitter.com/gelaineyyy",target="_blank") https://twitter.com/gelaineyyy
		.row
			.col-lg-3.col-md-3.col-sm-4.col-xs-12
				.text-center.team
					img(src="/images/jeromegagnonvoyer.png",class="img-responsive",alt="Jérôme Gagnon-Voyer")
			.col-lg-9.col-md-9.col-sm-8.col-xs-12
				h3 Jérôme Gagnon-Voyer
				p Jérôme is a seasoned technical consultant and developer, and serves as a founder and in-house technology expert for ChooseSocial.PH. He graduated with a degree in Computer Engineering from Laval University in Québec (Canada) and has more than 5 years' comprehensive consulting experience for big players across Canada and the US within a wide range of industries. He's no stranger to entrepreneurship – in addition to large corporations, he's also worked with small to medium-sized tech companies in Toronto, interned at a start-up in Silicon Valley, and also managed his own IT consulting business. 
				br
				p Jérôme isn't just a tech guy, though! He also worked as national VP of Communications for the global NGO, AIESEC, where he led marketing and IT initiatives and also discovered his passion for social entrepreneurship. In his spare time, Jérôme uses his powers for good by working pro bono on a range of technology projects!

