					a(href="http://www.gagnonvoyer.com",target="_blank") http://www.gagnonvoyer.com
	h2 What's a social enterprise? 
	.panel.panel-default
		.panel-body
			| The formal definition of a social enterprise is hard to pin down and may vary depending who you're talking to. Social enterprises can be for-profit, non-profit, co-operative, or charitable organizations – but to keep things simple, we define a social enterprise as a business that aims to achieve two things: 
	.row
		.col-lg-3.col-md-3.col-md-offset-3.col-sm-6.col-xs-6
			.thumbnail.text-center
				i.fa.fa-thumbs-up.bigicon
				.caption
					h3 Do good
		.col-lg-3.col-md-3.col-sm-6.col-xs-6
			.thumbnail.text-center
				i.fa.fa-line-chart.bigicon
				.caption
					h3 Be financially sustainable
	.panel.panel-default
		.panel-body
			| Our definition may sound simple, but we take it seriously. All the organizations that you will discover here are not only 
			strong proudly doing work in the Philippines 
			| but will also:
	.list-group
		.list-group-item.list-group-item-info
			h4.list-group-item-heading Have the cause be at the centre of the business
			p.list-group-item-text It will primarily exist and operate in order to improve a social or environmental cause or mission
		.list-group-item
			h4.list-group-item-heading Use market-based strategies to sustain their work
			p.list-group-item-text It will primarily fund itself through commercial activities or trade in order to remain financially sustainable
		.list-group-item.list-group-item-info
			h4.list-group-item-heading Be able to act independently
			p.list-group-item-text It will not be dependent on government grants or public donations in order to operate
		.list-group-item
			h4.list-group-item-heading Re-invest a percentage of its profits back into the cause or local community
			p.list-group-item-text The social mission/cause and the business itself are inextricably linked, so as the business and profits grow, the benefits to the impacted communities grow as well. 
	.panel.panel-default
		.panel-body 
			h5 Want to learn more? 
			| We're not the only ones crazy about social enterprise. 
			a(href="http://www.socialenterprise.org.uk/about/about-social-enterprise", target="_blank") Social Enterprise UK 
			| is doing great work and offers excellent resources for those of you interested in learning more about social enterprises or starting your own. 
	h2 But Why 
		em Choose Social 
		| Enterprise? 
	.whitebox
		p We believe all organizations need to be financially sustainable in order to scale up their impact, and we're big believers that social enterprises are the way to building a society where everyone profits. We want to foster and support organizations that are changing the business landscape – organizations that think like smart and savvy businesses in order to grow the bottom line: their social impact.
		br
		p So whether you are looking to start an organization, support one, or work for one – whatever it may be, consider choosing a social enterprise – because when you choose social, everyone wins.

